<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-93-0572 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper compares the characteristics and costs of the main kinds ofurban transit systems, including buses, trains, light rail, rapid rail,and suburban rail systems. It looks at the implications involved in settingup new transient systems. Provides a series of checks to ensure thatimportant questions are not overlooked; for example, the ability of thesystem to meet changing demands, revenue problems, the relative sophisticationof systems, financing and cost recovery, and the environmental impact.</TEXT></DOC>